node.text:
If you started your week off beer-prepping instead of meal-prepping, well, same! And lucky for all of us, our friends at @hopculturemag have some quick and easy beer-centric recipes to spice up your week. Like this Beer Cheese Dip! 🧀🍺

INGREDIENTS
1.5 cup cheddar cheese
1/2 cup mozzarella
8 oz. cream cheese
2 tsp garlic powder
1.5 tbsp Dijon mustard
1/4 cup beer (lager or IPA)

DIRECTIONS
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
2. In a medium bowl, combine cheddar cheese, mozzarella, cream cheese, garlic powder, and Dijon mustard and mash together until completely mixed
3. Add 1/4 cup of beer
4. Transfer to baking dish and bake until cheese bubbles
5. Enjoy with pretzels, tortilla chips, or veggies

Tag a friend you'd house this dip with.

node.title: How To Make Beer Cheese Dip with Hop Culture

node.text: So "I Remember My First Check-In" is a sour beer? YES! Why? Because we love data and letting it speak for itself! After looking back over 10 years of Untappd data with @dogfishhead we found that sours had the highest increase in check-ins year over year (163%), a consistent average rating of 3.9 or above, and an average sentiment score of 72% positive among users who had left a review for beer of that style.

node.text:
Recognized for its rich, strong style, the Imperial stout has an equally rich and strong history. Originally brewed by major porter brewers in London for export to the Baltic countries and Russia, the "extra stout" porter gained popularity in the late 18th century. Bigger is better, an adage that the world of craft beer has really taken to heart. While there are countless fantastic versions here are Untappd's 5 Highest Rated Imperial / Double Stouts of 2021 so far! Link in bio to read more.

2. Double Barrel VSOD (2020) - @revbrewchicago
3. Anniversary Bourbon County Brand Stout - @gooseisland

node.text:
📺 VIRTUAL HAPPY HOUR 📺 This Thursday, join us for a chat with Maíra Kimura, Co-founder and Brewer at @japascervejaria, in São Paulo, Brazil — a Nipo-Brazilian all-female brewery!

Maíra Kimura graduated in 2011 in the British Brewing Technology course at Brewlab, England, having also obtained the brewer certificate from the Institute of Brewing Distilling in the same year. Back in Brazil in 2012, she also graduated at SENAI's Advanced Brewing Technology course and Doemens’ Beer Sommelier. She was a founding partner of 2cabeças, and is now one of the brewers of Japas Cervejaria, a brewery formed by three Japanese-descendant women who produce beers with Japanese and Brazilian ingredients and themes. 

Tune in for @hopcultureken’s chat with Maíra this Thursday at 7pm ET on YouTube. Don't forget to hit that subscribe button while you’re there! 💥

node.text:
It's time for a fun story! 🥳 But first: if you haven't heard, the subject of our story — @weatheredsoulsbrewing — will be joining us at Untappd Beer Festival: San Diego. The brewery is known for its decadent stouts, refreshing lagers, and kickstarting the #BlackIsBeautifulBeer Project, one of the craft brewing industry's most successful justice initiatives to date. Don't wait! Grab your tickets for the festival now via the link in the bio. 

Okay, now the story! After moving to San Antonio for a banking job, Weathered Souls Co-Founder and Head Brewer @weatheredsoulsbrewing_marcus was involved in a car accident (stick with us — this story has a happy ending!). Baskerville was okay, and since he lived close to the office, he didn't use his insurance money to buy a new car. Instead, he bought the equipment necessary to get into his new hobby... homebrewing! Talk about dedication. Fast forward and Baskerville is 1/3 of the founding team behind Weathered Souls. And because of the brewery's success, he was able to quit his job in banking and now works in the brewing industry full-time. Dreams do come true! 

How did you get into homebrewing? Let us know in the comments.

node.text:
You’re extra special. Yes, you are! Traditionally, ESB stands for Extra Special Bitter. But, this beer has a pretty confusing history. A very close cousin to an English IPA, ESB was a forerunner catch-all for most early English beers. Ahead of its time, new ESB styles erupted as brewing methods evolved and brewers became more technical. While most still use an English yeast strain to coax out that traditional flavor, you can find American brewers putting their own take on this beer style as well, today. 

This week we're drinking Morland Old Speckled Hen (@oldspeckledhen_official) from Greene King to unlock the “You’re Extra Special” badge, earned by checking-in to five different beers with the style of Extra Special / Strong Bitter or English Bitter! We also highlight Jackalope Brewing Company - The Ranche in Nashville, TN (@jackalopebrew) as our Verified Venue of the Week, and shout out Rotunda Brewing Company (@rotundabrewingcompany) and New Anthem Beer Project (@newanthembeer) for crafting the best beers we had this week. Catch the latest episode on YouTube (link in bio) or listen wherever you get your podcasts.

Today, lagers are actually the world's most popular style of beer! Now, that's due in large part to the popularity of macro lagers such as Bud Light, Miller Lite, Modelo, Coors, and Corona. But craft brewers have been reclaiming this historical style and churning out their own incredible versions. From a rice lager with lime to an easy, breezy version steeped with lemongrass, here are Untappd's 5 Highest-Rated American Lagers of 2021 so far! Link in bio to read more.

Join us on a trip across the pond in the latest episode of Stocked Up! 

New York-born Peter Tavolacci (@beerwithabackdrop) works at Bianca Road Brew Co. in London, England, which got started after the owner biked 6,000km (3,728 miles, for you Yankees) across the United States, trying beers from the best breweries between Los Angeles and Miami. He shows off some of his collection of UK-centric beers including a double IPA from Gravity Well, Untappd’s highest rated brewery in London, and the famous Westvleteren 12, one of the highest rated beers in the world! Swipe up to watch the full episode on YouTube.

- Meet and greets with the brewers
- VIP-only tappings and guided tastings from Definitive Brewing Company, The Bruery and Crowns & Hops
- VIP-only beers (including pours from Horus Aged Ales, Tripping Animals, and Vitamin Sea Brewing)
- A special Untappd gift

Grab your VIP or GA tickets now via the link in the bio!

node.text: Take a trip to London with @beerwithabackdrop for Stocked Up. Full episode dropping on Saturday at 10:00 AM EST. Peter will be showing off some of his collection of UK-centric beers including a double IPA from Gravity Well, Untappd’s highest rated brewery in London, and the famous Westvleteren 12, one of the highest rated beers in the world!
